Cook bacon in a large, deep skillet over medium heat until crisp; remove from pan and drain on paper toweling. Add zucchini to skillet; cook and stir over medium-high heat about 3 minutes or until crisp-tender. Add rice, beans, and corn to pan. Cook and stir until heated through. Spoon rice and bean mixture into 2 large bowls. Top with turkey, bacon, avocado, radish, green onion, and cilantro. Top with salsa and a squeeze of lime.